tiaraIpMib.name: tiaraIpMib
tiaraIpMib.contactinfo: Tiara Networks Customer Support 525 Race Street, Suite 100, San Jose, CA 95126 USA Tel: +1 408-216-4700 Fax: +1 408-216-4701 E-mail: support@tiaranetworks.com
tiaraIpMib.description: This MIB defines objects for IP addressable interfaces and the static routing table.

tiaraIpRoutingEnable.name: tiaraIpRoutingEnable
tiaraIpRoutingEnable.description: This object toggles between the IP routing and the IP muxing modes. If the IP routing mode is disabled, the IP muxing mode is enabled. If the IP routing mode is enabled, the IP muxing mode is disabled.

tiaraIpIfTable.name: tiaraIpIfTable
tiaraIpIfTable.description: The TiaraIpIfTable defines objects for IP addressable interfaces that are currently configured on the Tiara system. It maps a unique index value to each interface.

tiaraIpIfTableEntry.name: tiaraIpIfTableEntry
tiaraIpIfTableEntry.description: An entry in the TiaraIpIfTable that defines objects for a particular IP interface.

tiaraIpIfIndex.name: tiaraIpIfIndex
tiaraIpIfIndex.description: This value identifies a particular IP interface and serves as an index for the tiarIpIfTable.

tiaraIpIfName.name: tiaraIpIfName
tiaraIpIfName.description: A unique name associated with an IP interface.

tiaraIpIfAddr.name: tiaraIpIfAddr
tiaraIpIfAddr.description: The unique IP address of an IP interface.

tiaraIpIfMask.name: tiaraIpIfMask
tiaraIpIfMask.description: The network mask associated with an IP interface.

tiaraIpIfPeerAddr.name: tiaraIpIfPeerAddr
tiaraIpIfPeerAddr.description: The IP address of the peer which is the other end of a point-to-point link. The peer IP address object is only valid for a WAN or point-to-point interface.

tiaraIpIfType.name: tiaraIpIfType
tiaraIpIfType.description: This object identifies the type of interface as either Ethernet or WAN.

tiaraStaticRouteTable.name: tiaraStaticRouteTable
tiaraStaticRouteTable.description: A list of static route table entries for this entity. The following variables are required for row creation: tiaraStaticRouteIndex = 65535 tiaraStaticRouteNetworkAddr = Destination IP address tiaraStaticRouteNetworkMask = Subnet mask tiaraStaticRouteGatewayAddr = Next hop IP address tiaraStaticRouteNoOfHops = Number of hops or metric tiaraStaticRouteRowStatus = createAndGo

tiaraStaticRouteEntry.name: tiaraStaticRouteEntry
tiaraStaticRouteEntry.description: A single static route entry in the static route table.

tiaraStaticRouteIndex.name: tiaraStaticRouteIndex
tiaraStaticRouteIndex.description: A numeric index for static route table entries. This index is internally generated by the SNMP agent, and it uniquely identifies a single entry in the table. To create a row in the table, use the invalid value 65535 for this variable. To query any variable in this table, use this variable, which can be found for a given (network address-network mask-gateway address) tuple using the snmp-walk operation.

tiaraStaticRouteNetworkAddr.name: tiaraStaticRouteNetworkAddr
tiaraStaticRouteNetworkAddr.description: The destination IP address of this route. This can be either a complete host address for one particular host or or a network address for all the hosts on that network. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 for the network address is considered a default route.

tiaraStaticRouteNetworkMask.name: tiaraStaticRouteNetworkMask
tiaraStaticRouteNetworkMask.description: The network mask associated with the network address

tiaraStaticRouteGatewayAddr.name: tiaraStaticRouteGatewayAddr
tiaraStaticRouteGatewayAddr.description: This can either be the IP address of a next hop router or the IP address of a directly connected network. The next hop router receives datagrams from the Tiara system and forwards them to the final destination. This can also be an interface name.

tiaraStaticRouteNoOfHops.name: tiaraStaticRouteNoOfHops
tiaraStaticRouteNoOfHops.description: The number of hops for this route.

tiaraStaticRouteRowStatus.name: tiaraStaticRouteRowStatus
tiaraStaticRouteRowStatus.description: Used to configure or delete a static route. To configure a route, set the value of this object to createAndGo. To delete a route, set the value of this object to destroy.
